GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/documents/a1d0c0de-0002-4b2b-9bbb-000000000002/download



### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### PDF Form Builder — API smoke test
### Every successful write below is stored in HANA (the deployed HDI container).
###
### SETUP (one time): get credentials with these two CF commands:
###     cf create-service-key pdf-form-builder-uaa apikey
###     cf service-key       pdf-form-builder-uaa apikey
### The second command prints JSON. Copy three values into the variables below:
###     "clientid"     -> @clientid
###     "clientsecret" -> @clientsecret
###     "url"          -> @tokenUrl
###
### HOW TO RUN: click the little "Send Request" link that appears above each
### request, top to bottom. Run #1 first (it fetches the token the others use).
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

@srv = https://bb2bd51ctrial-dev-pdf-form-builder-srv.cfapps.us10-001.hana.ondemand.com
@tokenUrl = https://bb2bd51ctrial.authentication.us10.hana.ondemand.com
@clientid = sb-pdf-form-builder!t662288
@clientsecret = 


### 1) Get an access token  (run this one FIRST)
# @name login
POST {{tokenUrl}}/oauth/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded
Authorization: Basic {{clientid}}:{{clientsecret}}

grant_type=client_credentials


### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### Store a PDF by POSTing it. No rendering, no token needed.
### The stored row appears in the Documents tab; open it to view the PDF.
###
### Put a PDF file next to this .http file (any PDF works) and set its name in
### the  < ./yourfile.pdf  line below.
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

@srv = https://bb2bd51ctrial-dev-pdf-form-builder-srv.cfapps.us10-001.hana.ondemand.com


### 1) Upload a PDF as the raw body (simplest)
# @name upload
POST {{srv}}/api/v1/documents?fileName=aurora-test.pdf&documentNumber=AC-2026-0481
Content-Type: application/pdf



### 2) Alternative: send it as JSON base64 (if you prefer)
POST {{srv}}/api/v1/documents
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fileName": "meridian-test.pdf",
  "documentNumber": "MRD-INV-77310",
  "contentBase64": "PASTE_BASE64_OF_A_PDF_HERE"
}


### 3) Verify: download the one you just stored (opens/saves the PDF)
###    Replace the id with "documentId" from request #1's response.
GET {{srv}}/api/v1/documents/PASTE_documentId/download
